<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="99" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="99">
&quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambold &amp; Pietschm., Bibliotheca Lichenologica 34: 239" authorityYear="1989" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Immersaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Immersaria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Immersaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Immersaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Immersaria iranica" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="iranica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Immersaria iranica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has lecanorine apothecia, a distinct epinecral layer and halonate ascospores (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0024282911000077" author="Valadbeigi, T" journalOrPublisher="Lichenologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="203 - 208" refId="B23" refString="Valadbeigi, T, Sipman, H, Rambold, G, 2011. The genus Immersaria (Lecideaceae) in Iran, including I. iranica sp. nov. Lichenologist 43 (3): 203 - 208, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1017/S0024282911000077" title="The genus Immersaria (Lecideaceae) in Iran, including I. iranica sp. nov." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0024282911000077" volume="43" year="2011">Valadbeigi et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The materials from China are in accordance with the materials of Iran, based on comparisons with the original descriptions and the photographs given by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0024282911000077" author="Valadbeigi, T" journalOrPublisher="Lichenologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="203 - 208" refId="B23" refString="Valadbeigi, T, Sipman, H, Rambold, G, 2011. The genus Immersaria (Lecideaceae) in Iran, including I. iranica sp. nov. Lichenologist 43 (3): 203 - 208, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1017/S0024282911000077" title="The genus Immersaria (Lecideaceae) in Iran, including I. iranica sp. nov." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0024282911000077" volume="43" year="2011">Valadbeigi et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. The characters of this species are consistent with the new genus and the phylogenetic results showed that it was clustered with species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, it was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is currently known from Iran and China.
</paragraph>
